Not to steal J.B.&#39;s flame, but I think this is what you may be looking for:

import junit.extensions.TestSetup;
import junit.framework.Test;

public class MyTestSetup extends TestSetup {
    public MyTestSetup(Test aTest) {
        super(aTest);
    }
    public void setUp() {
        ...do your one time setUp
    }
    public void tearDown() {
        ...do your one time tearDown
    }
    public static Test suite() {
        TestSuite suite = new TestSuite();
        suite.addTest(new MyTestSetup(&lt;TestCase&gt;);
        return suite;
    }
}

Add a main(String[]) if you aren&#39;t using an IDE inte*great*ed JUnit.

